  RELEVANCE: Establishes the empirical landscape of giving predictors. Critical for understanding whether asset-based or income-based norms align with actual giving behavior. The finding that both income and wealth predict giving, but through different mechanisms and at different life stages, directly informs the feasibility of different normative baselines. The psychological benefits mechanism (warm glow) is especially relevant for understanding intrinsic motivation versus utilitarian calculation.

